.START 

Thanks for the enlightening page-one article about the cruel and selfish people in Plentywood, Mont. ("One-Horse Town Has Five Ostriches That Lay $35 Eggs," Aug. 21).
Why don't those people get real jobs and stop mutilating, breaking up the families of, and killing animals?
You reported the unfortunate answer: "To make money." It's a frightening town that allows greed to rule over ethics. 

Leonard Spiegel 

Washington 

